Harry F. MURPHY et al. v. TOWN AND COUNTRY ESTATES, Inc. No. 3757. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 4, 1948. W. D. Jochems, of Wichita, Kan., for appellants. Fleeson, Gooing, Coulson & Kitch, of Wichita, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS,. Chief Judge, and SYMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed on motion of appellee, for failure to prosecute.
